{"type": "article", "id": 40472, "title": "这本“百科全书”，想带你发掘动植物界的彩虹｜这个设计了不起", "description": "我们每天都为你推荐几个最近发现的好设计。", "date": "2017-05-04T22:51:05Z", "super_tag": "", "tags": [{"id": 271, "name": "工业设计"}, {"id": 3263, "name": "Loewe"}, {"id": 40104, "name": "Lumdums"}, {"id": 40105, "name": "Julie Seabrook Ream"}], "category": 17, "column": 38, "author": 400262, "comment_count": 3, "praise_count": 197, "image": "img/article/article_show/20170504212918e2SCyunAo8jwkmbH.jpg", "contents": "<p nocleanhtml=\"true\">        <style type=\"text/css\"> p.p1 {margin: 0.0px 0.0px 0.0px 0.0px; line-height: 27.0px; font: 18.0px 'PingFang SC'; color: #363636} p.p2 {margin: 0.0px 0.0px 0.0px 0.0px; line-height: 32.0px; font: 18.0px 'PingFang SC'; color: #363636; min-height: 25.0px} p.p3 {margin: 0.0px 0.0px 0.0px 0.0px; line-height: 32.0px; font: 18.0px 'PingFang SC'; color: #363636} span.s1 {font-kerning: none} </style>  </p><p>「这个设计了不起」的微信公众号上线啦，直接搜索「BestDesign」或是「Qthings」就可以订阅，关注我们每日发现的新鲜好设计。</p><h3>Encyclopedia of Rainbows by Julie Seabrook Ream</h3><p>当被问及最喜欢哪种颜色时，我们多少都会有一些偏爱，而对无法割舍任何一种颜色的美国艺术家 <a href=\"https://www.instagram.com/hey_jules_studio/\" rel=\"nofollow\">Julie Seabrook Ream</a> 而言，只有包罗万象的彩虹色系才能表达出她对色彩的执着。Ream 会从日常生活中搜罗各式各样的素材，随后再根据不同的物品种类制定出不同的排列方案，让每一道“彩虹”都变得独一无二。不久前，她和独立出版社 Chronicle Books 展开合作，将由动植物构成的图案集结成了一本彩虹百科。你可以通过<a href=\"https://www.amazon.com/Encyclopedia-Rainbows-World-Organized-Color/dp/145215533X/\" rel=\"nofollow\">链接</a>购买到这本新书，精装版售价为 11.70 美元。</p><div class=\"com-insert-images\"><figure style=\"margin:0;\">\r\n    <img src=\"img/uploads/20170504212934cVkfsuLTSyPAgoMz.jpg\" alt=\"\" data-ratio=\"1.000000\" data-format=\"jpeg\" class=\"\">\r\n</figure></div><div class=\"com-insert-images\"><figure style=\"margin:0;\">\r\n    <img src=\"img/uploads/2017050421293436qXnjbWkICo4tzw.jpg\" alt=\"\" data-ratio=\"1.000000\" data-format=\"jpeg\">\r\n</figure></div><div class=\"com-insert-images\"><figure style=\"margin:0;\">\r\n    <img src=\"img/uploads/20170504212934jCzlW0xPYAhJ2ska.jpg\" alt=\"\" data-ratio=\"1.000000\" data-format=\"jpeg\">\r\n</figure></div><div class=\"com-insert-images\"><figure style=\"margin:0;\">\r\n    <img src=\"img/uploads/20170504212935KuAfmjG2V9MYT5Sq.jpg\" alt=\"\" data-ratio=\"1.000000\" data-format=\"jpeg\">\r\n</figure></div><div class=\"com-insert-images\"><figure style=\"margin:0;\">\r\n    <img src=\"img/uploads/20170504212935DjVtiYBbgFOl1AWo.jpg\" alt=\"\" data-ratio=\"1.000000\" data-format=\"jpeg\">\r\n</figure></div><div class=\"com-insert-images\"><figure style=\"margin:0;\">\r\n    <img src=\"img/uploads/20170504212935ViANaL3FS1oOhzkX.jpg\" alt=\"\" data-ratio=\"1.000000\" data-format=\"jpeg\">\r\n</figure></div><h3>Lumdums</h3><p>来自香港的 Lumdums 是一个对旧物怀有特殊情结的手工品牌，设计团队在走遍了中古市场之后，将无人问津的破旧黑胶唱片收集起来，打造成手机壳、饰品和乐器配件。利用唱片上的音轨，旗下的星球主题以及限量手机壳都可以两两组合成一张完整版。你可以在<a href=\"http://www.lumdums.com/\" rel=\"nofollow\">官方网站</a>上购买到这些重生的黑胶唱片制品，售价从 360 港元起。</p><div class=\"com-insert-images\"><figure style=\"margin:0;\">\r\n    <img src=\"img/uploads/20170504213500RP4YMolDFcJI7EQj.jpeg\" alt=\"\" data-ratio=\"0.667362\" data-format=\"jpeg\" class=\"\">\r\n</figure></div><div class=\"com-insert-images\"><figure style=\"margin:0;\">\r\n    <img src=\"img/uploads/20170504213500Qj2yVBghNFqIASec.jpg\" alt=\"\" data-ratio=\"1.000000\" data-format=\"jpeg\">\r\n</figure></div><div class=\"com-insert-images\"><figure style=\"margin:0;\">\r\n    <img src=\"img/uploads/201705042135001DTEtm0WGrNnXy2s.jpg\" alt=\"\" data-ratio=\"1.000000\" data-format=\"jpeg\">\r\n</figure></div><div class=\"com-insert-images\"><figure style=\"margin:0;\">\r\n    <img src=\"img/uploads/20170504213501S9CBMxEAk5uqc3ol.jpeg\" alt=\"\" data-ratio=\"0.750293\" data-format=\"jpeg\">\r\n</figure></div><h3>Bear Bowl</h3><p>在发现市面上只有常规锅具的小号版供露营野炊使用后，一支由户外活动爱好者组成的设计团队开发了世界上第一款可以经过折叠直接塞进口袋的锅子。这个名为 Bear Bowl 的小锅在重量上和一部常见的手机接近，能装下约 1 升的水。折叠状态下就像是一个钱包，携带起来非常方便，而且使用后只要展开就能做到无死角清洁。这是它的<a href=\"https://www.kickstarter.com/projects/bearbowl/bear-bowl-worlds-first-pocket-cook-pot\" rel=\"nofollow\">众筹链接</a>，售价从 23 美元起。</p><div class=\"com-insert-images\"><figure style=\"margin: 0px;\" class=\"\">\r\n    <img src=\"img/uploads/20170504213822G4K9knza3F2rSOUx.gif\" alt=\"\" data-ratio=\"0.550000\" data-format=\"gif\" class=\"\">\r\n</figure></div><div class=\"com-insert-images\"><figure style=\"margin:0;\">\r\n    <img src=\"img/uploads/201705042138141hpcBCzYLNZ8DHgr.jpg\" alt=\"\" data-ratio=\"0.705882\" data-format=\"jpeg\">\r\n</figure></div><div class=\"com-insert-images\"><figure style=\"margin:0;\">\r\n    <img src=\"img/uploads/201705042138141JnfR5oQlxWPCrmh.jpg\" alt=\"\" data-ratio=\"0.750000\" data-format=\"jpeg\">\r\n</figure></div><h3>Bild 9 by Loewe</h3><p>德国电视品牌 <a href=\"https://www.loewe.tv/\" rel=\"nofollow\">Loewe</a> 的创意总监 Bodo Sperlein 以 Art Deco 和包豪斯风格为灵感，打造了一款旨在成为室内焦点的曲面电视 Bild 9。整台电视由号称比大部分智能手机更薄的屏幕和一个几何金属框架构成，框架内部还预留了空间用来隐藏电线，看上去简洁优雅。</p><div class=\"com-insert-images\"><figure style=\"margin:0;\">\r\n    <img src=\"img/uploads/20170504213910YZXf8UeKgsd932rt.jpg\" alt=\"\" data-ratio=\"0.666667\" data-format=\"jpeg\" class=\"\">\r\n</figure></div><div class=\"com-insert-images\"><figure style=\"margin:0;\">\r\n    <img src=\"img/uploads/201705042139101lpa3z5IMOWr7u4Y.jpg\" alt=\"\" data-ratio=\"0.666667\" data-format=\"jpeg\">\r\n</figure></div><div class=\"com-insert-images\"><figure style=\"margin:0;\">\r\n    <img src=\"img/uploads/20170504213912UmP7cf80ltBSkOGV.jpg\" alt=\"\" data-ratio=\"0.666667\" data-format=\"jpeg\">\r\n</figure></div><h3>TVERGAMES by Ivan Voznyak</h3><p>俄罗斯游戏连锁店 <a href=\"https://vk.com/tvergames\" rel=\"nofollow\">TVERGAMES</a> 不仅出售各类游戏和主机，也提供交换和维修服务。由设计师 <a href=\"http://www.artgeneracia.com/\" rel=\"nofollow\">Ivan Voznyak</a> 操刀的品牌形象包含了四个能让人联想到游戏按键的符号，同时又与连锁店提供的几种服务紧密结合在一起。</p><div class=\"com-insert-images\"><figure style=\"margin: 0px;\" class=\"\">\r\n    <img src=\"img/uploads/20170504213932USkjAxtDoMCRBFcG.png\" alt=\"\" data-ratio=\"0.600000\" data-format=\"png\" class=\"\">\r\n</figure></div><div class=\"com-insert-images\"><figure style=\"margin:0;\">\r\n    <img src=\"img/uploads/20170504213925hcGVsqLZ6Q2W8XpU.png\" alt=\"\" data-ratio=\"0.584167\" data-format=\"png\">\r\n</figure></div><div class=\"com-insert-images\"><figure style=\"margin:0;\">\r\n    <img src=\"img/uploads/20170504213925AQcEfYnB4ovDeNRa.png\" alt=\"\" data-ratio=\"0.600000\" data-format=\"png\">\r\n</figure></div><div class=\"com-insert-images\"><figure style=\"margin:0;\">\r\n    <img src=\"img/uploads/20170504213926isZ5BckQ19zvEO2h.png\" alt=\"\" data-ratio=\"0.600000\" data-format=\"png\">\r\n</figure></div><div class=\"com-insert-images\"><figure style=\"margin:0;\">\r\n    <img src=\"img/uploads/20170504213925VRKO4DeqQapZs9Sc.png\" alt=\"\" data-ratio=\"0.600000\" data-format=\"png\">\r\n</figure></div><h3>The Six Forgotten Giants by Thomas Dambo</h3><p>在过去三年的时间里，擅长以回收材料作为创作素材的丹麦艺术家 <a href=\"http://thomasdambo.com/\" rel=\"nofollow\">Thomas Dambo</a> 在世界各地制作了 25 座巨型雕塑。最近，他回到了家乡哥本哈根，并在周边的森林里用回收来的木材制作了 6 个巨人。在藏宝图的指引下，游客们可以在森林里寻找巨人的踪影。</p><div class=\"com-insert-images\"><figure style=\"margin:0;\">\r\n    <img src=\"img/uploads/20170504214005iJwd9VanFr8yeCMs.jpg\" alt=\"\" data-ratio=\"0.667000\" data-format=\"jpeg\" class=\"\">\r\n</figure></div><div class=\"com-insert-images\"><figure style=\"margin:0;\">\r\n    <img src=\"img/uploads/20170504214006lihJH12B05YMOtTj.jpg\" alt=\"\" data-ratio=\"0.667000\" data-format=\"jpeg\">\r\n</figure></div><div class=\"com-insert-images\"><figure style=\"margin:0;\">\r\n    <img src=\"img/uploads/20170504214006pJ7BKt4HNLrVqGAi.jpg\" alt=\"\" data-ratio=\"0.667000\" data-format=\"jpeg\">\r\n</figure></div><div class=\"com-insert-images\"><figure style=\"margin:0;\">\r\n    <img src=\"img/uploads/20170504214006l970XcyBfAK3txCn.jpg\" alt=\"\" data-ratio=\"1.500000\" data-format=\"jpeg\">\r\n</figure></div>"}